        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): auto-detect DM thread sessions",
        "body": "Fixes #86513\n\n## Summary\n\n- Add `auto` as the Telegram DM `threadReplies` default and expose it in schema, generated metadata, docs, and UI hints.\n- Use fresh `getMe.has_topics_enabled` capability data for auto DM topic routing, bypassing stale startup bot-info cache when auto is active.\n- Route inbound messages, native commands, plugin commands, callbacks, and session-state lookups through DM topic sessions when auto or explicit config requires it.\n- Preserve bound route session keys for auto-default routing while still honoring explicit `inbound`, `always`, `requireTopic`, and topic config isolation.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/bot.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.thread-binding.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-native-commands.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.dm-threads.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot/helpers.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/channel.gateway.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/config-schema.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/telegram/src/bot-handlers.runtime.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-native-commands.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot/helpers.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot/helpers.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-bundled-extension-oxlint.mjs`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint-shards.mjs --threads=8`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test.tsbuildinfo`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm config:channels:check`\n- `pnpm config:docs:check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Telegram DM messages with `message_thread_id` now use topic-scoped sessions by default when the bot reports `has_topics_enabled=true`.\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw CLI/runtime with isolated `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-pr-86542-real/openclaw.json` and `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/tmp/openclaw-pr-86542-real/state`; no Telegram credentials or test harness.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran OpenClaw CLI config validation and readback against an isolated config containing `channels.telegram.dm.threadReplies: \"auto\"`.\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```console\n$ OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-pr-86542-real/openclaw.json OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/tmp/openclaw-pr-86542-real/state pnpm openclaw config validate --json\n{\"valid\":true,\"path\":\"/tmp/openclaw-pr-86542-real/openclaw.json\"}\n$ OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-pr-86542-real/openclaw.json OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/tmp/openclaw-pr-86542-real/state pnpm openclaw config get channels.telegram.dm.threadReplies --json\n\"auto\"\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: OpenClaw accepted the new Telegram `auto` config in a real config file and read it back from the active isolated setup; the focused Telegram runtime regression set passes with 7 files and 261 tests.\nWhat was not tested: Live Telegram delivery with a real bot account and Crabbox/Testbox proof; Crabbox was blocked because the local binary failed/missing sanity checks.\n",
